name: Acquisitions Expert
oracle_text: When Acquisitions Expert enters the battlefield, target opponent reveals a number of cards from their hand equal to the number of creatures in your party. You choose one of those cards. That player discards that card. (Your party consists of up to one each of Cleric, Rogue, Warrior, and Wizard.)

name: Ancestral Vision
oracle_text:
Suspend 4—{U} (Rather than cast this card from your hand, pay {U} and exile it with four time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter. When the last is removed, cast it without paying its mana cost.)
Target player draws three cards.

name: Ancient Grudge
oracle_text:
Destroy target artifact.
Flashback {G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
flavor_text: The time rifts remind Yavimaya of the enemies of its past and provide fresh fuel for its fires.

name: Ancient Stirrings
oracle_text: Look at the top five cards of your library. You may reveal a colorless card from among them and put it into your hand. Then put the rest on the bottom of your library in any order. (Cards with no colored mana in their mana costs are colorless. Lands are also colorless.)

name: Arc Blade
oracle_text:
Arc Blade deals 2 damage to any target. Exile Arc Blade with three time counters on it.
Suspend 3—{2}{R} (Rather than cast this card from your hand, you may pay {2}{R} and exile it with three time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter. When the last is removed, cast it without paying its mana cost.)

name: Assassinate
flavor_text: The rulers of old Dominaria kept assassins on retainer. However, the true loyalty of these master killers was always their peers. This elite community survived the fall of the old royal order.

name: Banishing Light
oracle_text: When Banishing Light enters the battlefield, exile target nonland permanent an opponent controls until Banishing Light leaves the battlefield.

name: Battering Sliver
flavor_text: Covered with hard shell-like plates, these slivers burrow through solid rock to carve out new nests for their hives.

name: Coal Stoker
oracle_text: When Coal Stoker enters the battlefield, if you cast it from your hand, add {R}{R}{R}.
flavor_text:
"The day is mine! I sent three such creatures against my foe, then watched as my magefire popped her soldiers like overripe spleenfruits."
—Dobruk the Unstable, pyromancer

name: Coral Trickster
oracle_text:
Morph {U} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)
When Coral Trickster is turned face up, you may tap or untap target permanent.
flavor_text: They wait in darkened depths, laughing eagerly.

name: Crookclaw Transmuter
oracle_text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
Flying
When Crookclaw Transmuter enters the battlefield, switch target creature's power and toughness until end of turn.

name: Dark Withering
oracle_text:
Destroy target nonblack creature.
Madness {B} (If you discard this card, discard it into exile. When you do, cast it for its madness cost or put it into your graveyard.)

card_faces.name: Dead
card_faces.oracle_text: Dead deals 2 damage to target creature.

card_faces.name: Gone
card_faces.oracle_text: Return target creature you don't control to its owner's hand.

name: Deadly Grub
oracle_text:
Vanishing 3 (This creature enters the battlefield with three time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter from it. When the last is removed, sacrifice it.)
When Deadly Grub dies, if it had no time counters on it, create a 6/1 green Insect creature token with shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)

name: Orcish Cannonade
oracle_text:
Orcish Cannonade deals 2 damage to any target and 3 damage to you.
Draw a card.
flavor_text:
"No ready! No aim! Just fire!"
—Scarback Plagg, orcish captain

name: Pallid Mycoderm
oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, put a spore counter on Pallid Mycoderm.
Remove three spore counters from Pallid Mycoderm: Create a 1/1 green Saproling creature token.
Sacrifice a Saproling: Each creature you control that's a Fungus or a Saproling gets +1/+1 until end of turn.

name: Paradise Plume
oracle_text:
As Paradise Plume enters the battlefield, choose a color.
Whenever a player casts a spell of the chosen color, you may gain 1 life.
{T}: Add one mana of the chosen color.
flavor_text: A last wisp of paradise in a fallen world.

name: Piracy Charm
oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Target creature gains islandwalk until end of turn. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
• Target creature gets +2/-1 until end of turn.
• Target player discards a card.

name: Pit Keeper
oracle_text: When Pit Keeper enters the battlefield, if you have four or more creature cards in your graveyard, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor_text: "The undead are not 'awakened.' They are evicted when there is no room left in the pit for more bodies."

name: Poultice Sliver
oracle_text: All Slivers have "{2}, {T}: Regenerate target Sliver."
flavor_text:
"Its broad claw suggests a chitinous shield, but in fact it conceals glands that secrete a remarkably swift healing agent."
—Rukarumel, field journal
